How to check if git is available on your system?

Answer: git --version
How to initialize a new Git repository?

Answer:
sh
Copy code
git init project
cd project
How to tell git about your name and email?

Answer:
sh
Copy code
git config --global user.name "<your name>"
git config --global user.email "<your email>"
How to add a file to the staging area?

Answer: git add <file>
How to remove a file from the staging area?

Answer: git reset HEAD -- <file>
How to make a commit?

Answer: git commit -m "Commit message"
How to send your changes to a remote repository?

Answer: git push
What is the difference between clone and pull?

Answer:
The git clone command is used when you want to download an existing Git repository to your local computer.
The git pull command is used when you want to update your local repository with changes made by another developer/team member in the remote repository.
